{
  "doc_id": "3742",
  "text": "Rasmussen et al. [CITATION_1] (rated as a level B quality) compared the effects of combined MT1 (in a side-lying position at the lumbar level of reduced movement) with exercises (two different extension exercises performed as often as possible during the day and at least once per hour), to the extension exercises alone in patients with chronic LBP classified as QTF 1-3. Both groups showed clinically relevant back and leg pain reduction, and no difference between the groups could be observed at the one month and one year follow-ups. Importantly, four patients in the intervention group and three in the control group reported worsening of back pain after 4 weeks, 3 months and one year.",
